<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,943,1400]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
HABITAT. The Iranian specimens were caught in “... a gravelled site on gypsum foothills with 
<taxonomicName box="[1227,1436,1196,1221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Alhagi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="camelorum">
